# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# InnoCooks v2 — environment
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values you need.
# `.env.local` is git-ignored; this `.env.example` is the documented template.
#
# NOTE: this site is a STATIC EXPORT (next.config.ts → output: "export"), so it
# has no server of its own. The contact form therefore talks to ONE external
# endpoint that you choose. Anything prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_ is shipped to the
# browser — only ever put PUBLIC values here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Contact form endpoint ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where the "Get in touch" form POSTs its JSON enquiry.
# Leave EMPTY to keep the zero-backend default (a structured mailto: opens the
# visitor's email app). Set it to switch the form to a real POST.
#
# Pick ONE of these patterns:
#
#   • Your own backend / serverless function (recommended for full control):
#       NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=https://api.innocooks.com/contact
#     Your handler receives JSON:
#       { name, email, business, budget, message, source, submitted_at }
#     and should: validate, rate-limit, then send mail (Resend/SendGrid/SMTP)
#     or store it. Keep all secrets (API keys, SMTP passwords) on the server —
#     NEVER in a NEXT_PUBLIC_ var.
#
#   • Formspree (https://formspree.io):
#       NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=https://formspree.io/f/xxxxxxxx
#
#   • Web3Forms (https://web3forms.com) — also set the access key below:
#       NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=https://api.web3forms.com/submit
#
#   • Getform / Basin / Formcarry: paste the endpoint they give you.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_ENDPOINT=

# Optional. Only needed by services that authenticate with a PUBLIC access key
# sent in the request body (e.g. Web3Forms). Domain-locked + rate-limited on
# their side, so it is safe to expose. Leave empty otherwise.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTACT_ACCESS_KEY=
